⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Impa
node ZEL · ZEL · ⟦Impa:ZEL:e84cb5⟧

WHO   — Impa — the Sheikah
WHAT  — The royal guardian — sentinel of Zelda and the bloodline, keeper of Sheikah lore and secret ways, a warrior of the shadow who teaches, shelters, and defends the goddess's chosen princess.
WHERE — ZEL · The Legend of Zelda  Framework inputs: The Legend of Zelda (the saga entire)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the Sheikah are sworn to the crown of Hyrule; because the princess who bears the goddess's wisdom must be kept alive against the dark; because some must stand in the shadow so the light may rule, and Impa is that shadow's faithful blade.
HOW   — By the warrior's discipline of the Sheikah, by hidden craft and the dance of the shadow, by counsel and song and the secrets passed down her people's line — and by an unbending loyalty that no age has broken.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the shadow that guards the light — sworn to the bloodline, keeper of its secrets, the blade that stands between the princess and the dark.

